      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEAFICE (5) resumes from a spell of three months. Could only manage to finish tenth at the latest run over 1230m at Albany. Good effort to kick-off last prep when in the money at Bunbury over 1100m. Looks the one to beat. RAY'S SAUCE (1) has been in the placings at his last two starts, finishing third last time when he was in the firing line all the way over 1300m at Port Hedland. Finds a perfect assignment and can get the job done. LADY MAYFLOWER (4) lined up for new trainer Leigh Murray last start and was having her first attempt on a dirt track when sixth, beaten 8 lengths, at Broome over 1200m. In the mix. DUOPOLY (7) was beaten a long way when tenth over 1300m at Port Hedland last time out. Nicely placed to find some form. ",
